# Release and PR workflow

## Always branch + PR — never direct `main`

- **Every change** that lands on `main` goes through a **pull request**: branch → commit → push **branch** → user opens PR in GitHub UI (compare URL).
- **Never** commit on `main`, **never** `git push origin main`, unless the user explicitly asks for a direct-main exception.
- Applies to **all** work: features, fixes, docs, planning updates, release cuts (`release/<version>`), CHANGELOG-only edits.
- When finishing requested work: push the **feature branch** and give the compare URL plus suggested PR title and body. Do not merge; the user merges in GitHub.
- **Releases:** use `release/<version>` branch + PR; after merge, `git pull` on `main`, then optional `git tag` (see below).

## CHANGELOG and roadmap

- Every PR must update `CHANGELOG.md` under `[Unreleased]` (CI enforces this).
- Planned work belongs in `docs/ROADMAP.md`; release steps in `docs/RELEASE.md`.
- Reference ROADMAP task numbers in the PR description; check boxes when done.
- Before a release cut: milestone complete, version bumped in `package.json`, CHANGELOG section dated — all via **release/** PR.

## Releases — CHANGELOG + git tag only

- **Source of truth:** [CHANGELOG.md](../CHANGELOG.md) (dated sections) and optional **annotated git tags** (`v0.3.1`, …) on `main` **after** the release PR is merged.
- **Do not** ask the user to create a **GitHub Release** (Releases UI, `gh release create`, or github.com/releases/new).
- After a release PR merges: update `immediate-nest-step.md` and [docs/RELEASE.md](../docs/RELEASE.md); link to **CHANGELOG anchors**.

## Git only — never `gh`

- **Do not run `gh`** (GitHub CLI) for PRs, issues, checks, releases, or API queries.
- Use **git** for branch, commit, `git push origin <branch>`, and post-merge `git tag` / `git push origin vX.Y.Z`.
- Compare URL after push: `https://github.com/peterkrentel/mcp-tool-guard/compare/main...<branch>`
